line by line

g for global replacement, else only the first one is replaced

regular expressions

char  matches itself
. 	any char
*	matches a sequence of chars, 0 or more
\+	matches a 1+ sequence of chars
\?	0 or 1 characters
\{i\} 	As *, but matches exactly i sequences
\{i,j\}
    Matches between i and j, inclusive, sequences
... etc...

see README in each directory 



